task.summary:
PR fixes
Added missing Generic specifications

Save desiredCapabilities with global session
* Instead of a static global session ID have a static instance of Session which contains the ID and the desiredCapabilities * Refactored Session and other methods that use Session to use this new format * Added routes GET /session/:sessionId and GET /sessions * Fixed bug in RouteMap; wasn't narrowing down route matches by method

Added NotYetImplemented handlers
* Added exception and handler for not yet implemented * Added a /session/:sessionId/timeouts route that calls the handler that throws not yet implemented * Fixed bugs in testRegex. The part of the regex should exclude / and the end should have optional trailing / * Added 'protected' to BaseResponse (no package-private)

Handle every Appium route that isn't implemented with special handler
* Added 'NotYetImplemented' exception and handler * Added every route and set the non-implemented ones to use that handler

Added duplicate route exception; fixed some todos
* Use the MediaType library to get application/json * Added exception handling to parseBody

Move /lib files over to main so can be accessed in unit tests
* When src files are in androidTest/ they can't be accessed by test/ * When src files are in main/ they can be accessed by androidTest/ and test/ * Moved the files back over to main (main still has no Android app so there still won't be an overhead of running an Android app inside of devices) * Added a unit Test for RouteDefinition.java * Doing this because I'll need to write unit tests to figure out how to write a custom method that gets the source of the app

Sets attributes on the XML element
* Added ViewAttributesEnum which enumerates all of the attributes we want to report on a View * Added ViewElement which translates a View into a Java object which contains these attributes * Fixed an error in the Stack Trace * Source.java uses the ViewElement to extract the attributes and then set them on the XML Element
Moved Source XML construction logic to it's own class
Stream bitmap to byte array rather than file

MESSAGE.value: Move getStackTrace to utility method
PR fix

Save desiredCapabilities with global session
* Instead of a static global session ID have a static instance of Session which contains the ID and the desiredCapabilities * Refactored Session and other methods that use Session to use this new format * Added routes GET /session/:sessionId and GET /sessions * Fixed bug in RouteMap; wasn't narrowing down route matches by method

Added NotYetImplemented handlers
* Added exception and handler for not yet implemented * Added a /session/:sessionId/timeouts route that calls the handler that throws not yet implemented * Fixed bugs in testRegex. The part of the regex should exclude / and the end should have optional trailing / * Added 'protected' to BaseResponse (no package-private)

Handle every Appium route that isn't implemented with special handler
* Added 'NotYetImplemented' exception and handler * Added every route and set the non-implemented ones to use that handler

Handles routes that aren't implemented
* Added not yet implemented handler and exception * Added every Appium route and made the non-implemented routes call that handler

Added duplicate route exception; fixed some todos
* Use the MediaType library to get application/json * Added exception handling to parseBody
Fixed broken routing regex

Move /lib files over to main so can be accessed in unit tests
* When src files are in androidTest/ they can't be accessed by test/ * When src files are in main/ they can be accessed by androidTest/ and test/ * Moved the files back over to main (main still has no Android app so there still won't be an overhead of running an Android app inside of devices) * Added a unit Test for RouteDefinition.java * Doing this because I'll need to write unit tests to figure out how to write a custom method that gets the source of the app

Added source handler endpoint
* Created model called ElementNode which stores data about a View and it's children. Serializes to XML. * Added a custom viewaction that uses some trickery to get the root view of the application * The handler takes the root view, passes it into elementNode and then serializes it to XML * The serialized XML is used in the endpoint

Added /source handler
* Added ElementNode model, which takes an instance of an Android view and turns it into a serializable object that has content-description and children (more to be added later) * Added RootViewFinder which trickily implements ViewAction to get a reference to the Root view in the app * Added source handler endpoint that passes the Root View into the ElementNode and serializes XML that is returned to the client
Typo fix

Set the element node names to the View's class name
* Added a visitor strategy to the ElementNode which translates the name of the element to it's class name (e.g.: instead of being called `elementNode` it might be called `android.widgets.TextView`) * Added a NodeJS unit test to test the /source endpoint (uses XMLDOM parser and XPath)
Use javax.xml instead of SimpleXML

Sets attributes on the XML element
* Added ViewAttributesEnum which enumerates all of the attributes we want to report on a View * Added ViewElement which translates a View into a Java object which contains these attributes * Fixed an error in the Stack Trace * Source.java uses the ViewElement to extract the attributes and then set them on the XML Element
Moved Source XML construction logic to it's own class

Added XPath as a selector strategy
* Updated SourceDocument to include a method that finds an Element by Xpath * Wrote a custom viewmatcher that finds an element by XPath * Added XPath as a selector strategy in Finder * Added a mocha test that tests finding an element by xpath and clicking on it
Codacy fix. Capitalize withXpath
Stream bitmap to byte array rather than file
Added /back endpoint

Sanitize the XML
* Renames classNames to simple class names (taken from uiautomator) * Scrub invalid characters from XML attributes
Changed simple class name back

Implemented the /element/:elementId/text endpoint
* Added a GetText class that takes a view interaction and then hackily gets it's view from it and returns the 'text' attribute
PR fixes
